00:01:09.884 --> 00:01:11.800
Close your eyes if you're
comfortable with it.

00:01:11.800 --> 00:01:14.330
And just notice the
sensations of your breath.

00:01:14.330 --> 00:01:15.716
This kind of
fundamental exercise

00:01:15.716 --> 00:01:17.840
underlies all the things
we're going to talk about.

00:01:17.840 --> 00:01:20.054
So just notice what it
feels like to breathe.

00:01:20.054 --> 00:01:21.970
We're breathing all the
time, but how often do

00:01:21.970 --> 00:01:24.300
we actually notice
what it feels like?

00:01:24.300 --> 00:01:27.650
So if that's the air passing
in and out of your nostrils,

00:01:27.650 --> 00:01:29.850
if that's the diaphragm
rising and falling,

00:01:29.850 --> 00:01:32.476
just try to tune in
on that sensation.

00:01:32.476 --> 00:01:34.100
And what's going to
happen, I guarantee

00:01:34.100 --> 00:01:36.199
you, after 5 seconds
or 30 seconds,

00:01:36.199 --> 00:01:37.490
is your mind's going to wander.

00:01:37.490 --> 00:01:39.720
You're going to wonder
what's for lunch after this,

00:01:39.720 --> 00:01:42.700
why is this guy talking to me,
why aren't we doing anything.

00:01:42.700 --> 00:01:43.830
And here's the whole game.

00:01:43.830 --> 00:01:46.670
When that moment happens, just
gently bring your attention

00:01:46.670 --> 00:01:47.589
back to the breath.

00:01:47.589 --> 00:01:48.880
It's just attentional training.

00:01:48.880 --> 00:01:51.140
So just try to return
the attention back

00:01:51.140 --> 00:01:52.720
to those physical sensations.

00:01:52.720 --> 00:01:55.907
Let's try it for just a
short little bit here.

