00:44:44.070 --> 00:44:47.780
of a heated debate on email with
a guy who's-- he's come after

00:44:47.780 --> 00:44:48.280
me.

00:44:48.280 --> 00:44:52.340
And he really thinks that
offering and promoting

00:44:52.340 --> 00:44:55.200
secular mindfulness
can actually do harm,

00:44:55.200 --> 00:44:58.410
and it actually is a way of
reinforcing the self instead

00:44:58.410 --> 00:45:00.120
of kind of breaking
down the self,

00:45:00.120 --> 00:45:03.180
as the origins of these
traditions would suggest we do.

00:45:03.180 --> 00:45:06.110
And what I say to
that is, I don't

00:45:06.110 --> 00:45:07.990
think anything's
getting lost, because I

00:45:07.990 --> 00:45:12.220
think this is something other
than the Shambala tradition.

00:45:12.220 --> 00:45:14.860
And this is something
other than the Buddhism

00:45:14.860 --> 00:45:16.110
that I studied in India.

00:45:16.110 --> 00:45:18.640
And this is something
other than what

00:45:18.640 --> 00:45:21.890
this guy is expecting of me.

00:45:21.890 --> 00:45:26.320
And can this, can
mindfulness, can

00:45:26.320 --> 00:45:29.200
secular mindfulness essentially
be a first step on a longer

00:45:29.200 --> 00:45:30.030
journey?

00:45:30.030 --> 00:45:31.030
Sure.

00:45:31.030 --> 00:45:33.970
But I'm not here trying
to offer a Trojan

00:45:33.970 --> 00:45:35.280
horse to Buddhist meditation.

00:45:35.280 --> 00:45:37.640
I don't think that's
what this is about.

00:45:37.640 --> 00:45:39.430
Instead, what I think
is-- mindfulness

00:45:39.430 --> 00:45:42.680
can help in all sorts
of very practical ways.

00:45:42.680 --> 00:45:44.510
And if it can make
people a little less

00:45:44.510 --> 00:45:47.700
stressed and a little
healthier and a little kinder,

00:45:47.700 --> 00:45:49.680
and if it can reduce
suffering on the margins

00:45:49.680 --> 00:45:53.990
and make businesses behave
a bit more responsibly,

00:45:53.990 --> 00:45:56.300
I don't see how we
can argue with that.

00:45:56.300 --> 00:45:59.720
And no one I've found is
presenting secular mindfulness

00:45:59.720 --> 00:46:02.680
as essentially kind of
traditional Buddhism

00:46:02.680 --> 00:46:03.410
in disguise.

00:46:03.410 --> 00:46:06.430
And I guess that's where
I would take umbrage with.

00:46:06.430 --> 00:46:09.300
This notion that these are
exactly the same things,

00:46:09.300 --> 00:46:12.680
I think, is how we
start to get in trouble.

00:46:12.680 --> 00:46:15.590
Instead, I recognize that
they're really robust,

00:46:15.590 --> 00:46:18.180
really rich, and
wonderful traditions,

00:46:18.180 --> 00:46:21.220
and that secular mindfulness,
Mindfulness Based Stress

00:46:21.220 --> 00:46:23.860
Reduction, what's being
practiced here and Goldman

00:46:23.860 --> 00:46:27.590
Sachs, it may have originally
taken its inspiration from some

00:46:27.590 --> 00:46:29.990
of these practices,
but I don't think

00:46:29.990 --> 00:46:32.820
it's trying to accomplish
the same goals either.

00:46:32.820 --> 00:46:35.410
But if it can, again, help
on the margins, that's

00:46:35.410 --> 00:46:36.591
a good thing, I'd say.

00:46:36.591 --> 00:46:37.340
I hope that helps.

00:46:37.340 --> 00:46:37.965
AUDIENCE: Yeah.

00:46:37.965 --> 00:46:39.470
Thanks.

00:46:39.470 --> 00:46:41.334
DAVID GELLES: Hi.

00:46:41.334 --> 00:46:43.530
AUDIENCE: Hi.

00:46:43.530 --> 00:46:46.450
You sort of lumped in yoga
together with meditation.

00:46:46.450 --> 00:46:51.180
And I had a question
specifically about that.

00:46:51.180 --> 00:46:55.070
I completely buy that yoga
works and that meditation works.

00:46:55.070 --> 00:46:56.720
But the reason it
works, in my mind,

00:46:56.720 --> 00:47:00.050
is because yoga, for example,
is a form of exercise.

00:47:00.050 --> 00:47:03.320
Is there any study
that compares yoga

00:47:03.320 --> 00:47:05.620
versus more traditional
forms of exercise

00:47:05.620 --> 00:47:07.909
and what's more effective there?

00:47:07.909 --> 00:47:10.200
DAVID GELLES: I don't know
the answer to that question,

00:47:10.200 --> 00:47:11.910
but you're right to
call me out on kind

00:47:11.910 --> 00:47:13.970
of lumping things together.

00:47:13.970 --> 00:47:16.570
What happens here--
mindfulness becomes

00:47:16.570 --> 00:47:18.610
kind of a very vague term.

00:47:18.610 --> 00:47:20.256
And in fact, I have
a whole passage

00:47:20.256 --> 00:47:21.880
in the book where I
kind of try to come

00:47:21.880 --> 00:47:24.590
to terms with what it is
we're actually talking about.

00:47:24.590 --> 00:47:26.320
I will say all the
studies I pointed

00:47:26.320 --> 00:47:28.430
to and all the research
that I include in my book

00:47:28.430 --> 00:47:32.360
is mostly about Mindfulness
Based Stress Reduction or kind

00:47:32.360 --> 00:47:34.570
of pure mindfulness
attentional training,

00:47:34.570 --> 00:47:36.200
what we practiced earlier on.

00:47:36.200 --> 00:47:38.760
Where yoga comes in--
it's often essentially--

00:47:38.760 --> 00:47:40.610
it's how people find
out about mindfulness.

00:47:40.610 --> 00:47:42.910
It's how both Mark and
Eileen Fisher, for example,

00:47:42.910 --> 00:47:44.140
came to the practice.

00:47:44.140 --> 00:47:47.570
And at Aetna, in some of the
studies, in some of the data

00:47:47.570 --> 00:47:51.340
they did, they lumped together
the results from both yoga

00:47:51.340 --> 00:47:52.340
and meditation practice.

00:47:52.340 --> 00:47:54.620
But I try to be
pretty deliberate

00:47:54.620 --> 00:47:57.820
about differentiating
between the two.

00:47:57.820 --> 00:48:00.660
Nonetheless, for kind
of a lay audience,

00:48:00.660 --> 00:48:05.390
it's often easy and
kind of helpful to group

00:48:05.390 --> 00:48:09.740
these complementary practices,
as they're known, together.

00:48:09.740 --> 00:48:11.680
I don't know the answer
to the yoga question.

00:48:11.680 --> 00:48:13.490
There's actually a
